[20260426-200512.6512]  
[20260426-200512.6513]  Converts from four possible input bases (including 10), to 29 possible output
[20260426-200512.6529]  bases. Strictly positional notation conversion, not for binary-to-text
[20260426-200512.6544]  encoding/decoding. (Though you can use the same common 2^N encoding bases such
[20260426-200512.6560]  as base32 or base64, as positional notation.)
[20260426-200512.6570]  
[20260426-200512.6570]  Syntax: convert-base-v1b  [optional args]  <NUMBER>  <OBASE>
[20260426-200512.6583]    Required arguments (in any order):
[20260426-200512.6591]      <NUMBER> .........: The input value to convert
[20260426-200512.6601]      <OBASE> ..........: The base to convert to (default 10 if not specified)
[20260426-200512.6617]    Optional arguments:
[20260426-200512.6622]      --ibase <base> ...: The input base (default 10 if not specified)
[20260426-200512.6637]      --from  <base> ...: Alias for '--ibase'
[20260426-200512.6646]      --obase <base> ...: Optional explicit flag for output base.
[20260426-200512.6660]      --to  <base> .....: Alias for '--obase'
[20260426-200512.6670]      --lcase ..........: Lower case (for bases with alpha and only one case)
[20260426-200512.6686]      --clipin .........: Use clipboard for input
[20260426-200512.6697]      --clipout ........: Use clipboard for output
[20260426-200512.6707]      --silent .........: No CLI output. Also sets --clipout.
[20260426-200512.6721]      --help, --about, --version [or -h, -a, -v]
[20260426-200512.6731]    Valid values for output <base>
[20260426-200512.6738]      Note: ST=Standard, PS=Pseudostandard, PUB=Published, C=Custom:
[20260426-200512.6752]          2      ST  aka Binary ................. 0,1
[20260426-200512.6764]          8      ST  aka Octal .................. 0-7
[20260426-200512.6775]         10      ST  aka Decimal [default] ...... 0-9
[20260426-200512.6786]         16      ST  aka Hexedecimal ............ 0-9, A-F
[20260426-200512.6798]         26      PS  One-case alphabetic ........ A-Z
[20260426-200512.6810]         32[r]   ST  RFC 4648 ¬І6 ................ A-Z, 2-7
[20260426-200512.6822]         32h     ST  RFC 4648 ¬І7, 'Base32Hex' ... 0-9, A-V
[20260426-200512.6834]         32c     PUB Crockford's Base32 ......... 0-9, A-Z no I, L, O, U
[20260426-200512.6850]         32ws    PUB Word-safe Base32 ........... 2-9, CFGHJMPQRVWX, cfghjmpqrvwx
[20260426-200512.6867]         36      PS  Just alphanum .............. 0-9, A-Z
[20260426-200512.6879]         38host  C   Valid *nix host and domain name characters
[20260426-200512.6892]         39user  C   Valid *nix username characters
[20260426-200512.6904]         45email C   Valid HTML5 <email> address characters
[20260426-200512.6916]         48jc1ws C   Base 32ws + unicode symbols
[20260426-200512.6927]         52      PS  Both-case alphabetic ....... A-Z, a-z
[20260426-200512.6939]         62      PS  All alphanum ............... 0-9, A-Z, a-z
[20260426-200512.6953]         64[r]   ST  RFC 4648 ¬І4 ................ A-Z, a-z, 0-9, +, /
[20260426-200512.6968]         64u     ST  RFC 4648 ¬І5, URL-safe ...... A-Z, a-z, 0-9, -, _
[20260426-200512.6983]         64h     PS  Hex like, URL-safe ......... 0-9, A-Z, a-z, -, _
[20260426-200512.6998]         64jc1   C   Base 62, +2 unicode symbols  0-9, A-Z, a-z,  Ю, ќї
[20260426-200512.7013]         64jc1ws C   Base 48jcw + more unicode symbols
[20260426-200512.7024]        128jc1ws C   Base 64jcw + more unicode symbols
[20260426-200512.7036]        128jc1   C   Base 64jc  + more unicode symbols
[20260426-200512.7048]        256jc1   C   Base 128jc + more unicode symbols
[20260426-200512.7060]        288jc1   C   Base 256jc + more unicode symbols
[20260426-200512.7072]      v1 backwards-compatiable 'incongruous' word-safe bases:
[20260426-200512.7085]         48v1compat, 64v1compat, 128v1compat
[20260426-200512.7095]    Valid values for --ibase:
[20260426-200512.7101]      2, 8, 10, 16, 36
